						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the Agnīśvara shrine in the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kōṉēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ: Year 29, 98th day.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records a gift of land as <hi rend="italic">iṟaiyili,</hi> made by the king, in Tiruvālanadurai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vikramachōḻach-chaturvvēdimaṅgalam to those who recited the <hi rend="italic">Mahābhārata</hi> in the village. A certain Villavadaraivan figures as signatory.</p>						

